items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Angry Catfish Wednesday social ride. Instagram. Discord. Website.

When: Wednesday Oct 1, 2025 rolling at 6:00 pm. First Wednesday of each month during cold weather months.

Start: Angry Catfish Bicycle Finish: Venn Brewing Company

Distance: ~15 miles. Pace: 12-13 mph.

Bring lights, dress for the weather. Led by: Alex & Adam

Some additional considerations as weather gets colder:
- Dress for the weather, we will ride even when the temperature gets real low. Layers, pogies, and toe warmers are your friends. Ask friends how they layer, experiment and enjoy the thrill of winter riding.
- Ride based on your comfort level - rides will be in the dark and can be icy/snowy. Studded and/or fat tires encouraged in the depths of winter. Lights required.

Led by: Alex & Adam.

See Discord link for ride updates.
items.location: Angry Catfish Bicycle, 2900 E 42nd St, Minneapolis, MN 55406, USA

items.description:
Race (alleycat) A Few Gears Eve. Instagram. 

When: Wednesday Dec 31, 2025 7:00 PM. Reg opens at 7pm, 7:45pm roll-out to secret start.

Start: Spot Bar (859 Randolph Ave, St. Paul)

Cost: Entry is $20 suggested donation, which will go 100% to Second Harvest Heartland. 

The fourteenth version of Saint Paul's longest running alley cat is back and better than ever!

For the race you'll need a bike, a pen, bike lights, your device, warm clothes, a backpack, money for drinks, curiosity, a playful attitude and a sense of wonder.  

The race will be no more than 20 miles with the proper number of hills to keep everyone warm. 

There is no requirement to drink alcohol, only to support the checkpoint hosting establishment. 

There will be prizes for the top finishers in three categories: Open, Women, and Gender Non Conforming.  There will also be a prize for DFL. 

After party with food, drink, sauna and a bonfire.
items.location: Spot Bar, 859 Randolph Ave, St Paul, MN 55102, USA

items.summary: Behind Bars Winter Solstice Light Ride
items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Behind Bars Winter Solstice Light Ride. Instagram.

When: Saturday Dec 20, 2025 5:00 PM. Roll at 5:15pm.

Start: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop. Finish: Modist Brewing Co.

Distance: up to 10 miles. Pace: casual, 10-12 mph. 

Adorn your bike in decorative holiday lights and join us for our 3rd annual Winter Solstice Light Ride @behindbarsbicycleshop. We will follow a festively lit riverfront/downtown route and end @modistbrewing Food can be ordered from a number of nearby restaurants to enjoy. I hear the pizza across the street @bricksworthbeer is excellent! A $50 Behind Bars Bicycle Shop merchandise gift card prize will go to the best decorated bike, chosen by shop ambassadors vote. Be bright to chase away the darkness.
items.location: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop, 208 13th Ave NE, Minneapolis, MN 55413, USA

items.location: TBD

items.description:
Distance: typically 5-15 miles. Pace: typically 5-15 mph. 

Join shop Ambassador Robin for some winter cycling adventures!

Due to variable weather, the details of each ride won't be shared until a few days before. The pace and distance of each ride will depend on the conditions.

"Adventure" can take on many forms, from interesting neighborhoods to technical off-road trails, so make sure the next ride is right for you and your bike.

Be prepared. Bring a helmet, lock, lights, a spare inner tube, and extra clothing. Ambassadors will be available for minor repairs, but you should have a backup plan in case of major issues (e.g. public transit).

Have a sense of adventure! Be ready for obstacles, uneven terrain, and possible route deviations.
items.location: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop, 208 13th Ave NE, Minneapolis, MN 55413, USA

items.summary: Solstice Sunrise Ride with Fast Casual
items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Solstice Sunrise Ride with Fast Casual. Instagram.

When: Sunday Dec 21, 2025 7:00 AM. Roll at 7:15am.

Start: Martin Olav Sabo Bridge. Finish: Cedar Lake (Point Beach on East side)

Distance: ~5 miles. Pace: 12-14 mph. 

A short ride for the shortest day of the year. Finish at Point Beach in time to catch the sunrise at 7:48 am.

We’ll roll together from sabo bridge to cedar lake for a wintery sunrise beach hang.Bring your friends and a warm beverage ☕️
items.location: Martin Olav Sabo Bridge, Minneapolis, MN 55407, USA
